OL,6,FBut Anita is not angry about the
OL,7,Fdamage done to her street from the
OL,8,Friot.
OL,10,FShe says she is angry because she
OL,11,Fcomplained for seven years about the
OL,12,Fanti-social behaviour of her
OL,13,Fneighbours, who, she says, were Roma,
OL,14,Fbut nobody listened, and instead she
OL,15,Fwas called a racist.
OL,17,FShe blames "the authorities and the
OL,18,Flandlords... because they didn't
OL,19,Flisten.
